  "prompt": "What are some university scams?",
  "response": "Here are some common university-related scams to be aware of:\n\n1. Fake Scholarship Offers\n- Scammers requesting upfront fees\n- Promises of guaranteed scholarships\n- Requests for personal/financial information\n\n2. Diploma Mill Scams\n- Offering fake degrees\n- Unaccredited online \"universities\"\n- Charging high fees for worthless credentials\n\n3. Financial Aid Fraud\n- Phishing emails requesting personal information\n- Fake FAFSA websites\n- Identity theft schemes\n\n4. International Student Recruitment Scams\n- Fraudulent admission offers\n- Fake student visa assistance\n- Charging excessive processing fees\n\n5. Online Course Scams\n- Fake online degree programs\n- Low-quality or non-existent courses\n- Misleading accreditation claims\n\n6. College Admission Consulting Scams\n- Promises of guaranteed admission\n- Charging excessive fees\n- Using fake credentials\n\n7. Student Loan Forgiveness Scams\n- Charging fees for free government programs\n- Promising immediate loan elimination\n- Collecting personal information fraudulently\n\nAlways research thoroughly, verify credentials, and be skeptical of offers that seem too good to be true.",
